Place a lightly oiled #baking sheet{} on top rack (for 4 servings, use 2 lightly oiled #baking sheets{} on top and middle racks) and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and halve @zucchini{1} lengthwise; thinly slice crosswise into half-moons. Halve @grape tomatoes{4%ounce}. Peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{2.5%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add zucchini and cook, stirring, until lightly browned and softened, ~{5-6%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Turn off heat.

> Wipe out pan for use in step 5.

While zucchini cooks, in a small #bowl{}, combine tomatoes, garlic, and a drizzle of olive oil. Season with salt and pepper.

In a second small bowl, combine @ricotta cheese{4%ounce}, half the lemon zest, ½ tsp olive oil (1 tsp for 4 servings), and lemon juice to taste. Season with salt and pepper.

Carefully place @flatbreads{2} on prepared sheet (divide between both prepared sheets for 4 servings). Evenly spread flatbreads with lemon ricotta. Top with zucchini and tomatoes, cut sides up.

Bake on top rack (top and middle racks for 4) until flatbreads are golden brown, ~{10-12%minutes}.

While flatbreads bake, heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in pan used for zucchini over medium-high heat. Add @prosciutto{2%ounce} in a single layer; sear until browned and crispy, ~{2-3%minutes} per side. (For 4 servings, cook in batches if necessary.)

> Press down on prosciutto with a spatula for even crisping. If prosciutto starts to brown too quickly, reduce heat to medium.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #paper-towel-lined plate{}.

Meanwhile, pick @green herb blend{1}(leaves only) from stems; roughly chop leaves. Mince chives. (Assuming @chives{})

Once flatbreads are done, garnish with parsley, chives, remaining lemon zest, and @chili flakes{1%teaspoon} to taste. Drizzle with @honey{2%teaspoon}, then slice into pieces.

Divide between plates and serve with any remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> Crumble prosciutto over flatbreads.